Description: Floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery cup or bowl; interior glazed black with impressed decoration: from centre, part of palmette, circle of enclosed carelessly struck ovules, linked palmettes, trace of circle of enclosed ovules; underside: reserved with two bands to outside if fragment and thin ring near centre; inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1672)
